46. Bf5 (46. Rb3 $1 $18 {was winning, but once again I had a time shortage and
played natural moves instead.} Bxd4+ (46... Ba7 47. h5 Kf8 48. h6) 47. Kxd4
Ra4+ 48. Kxd5 Rxg4 49. f4 $1) 46... Kf8 47. Rb3 Re1+ 48. Kd2 Ba5+ 49. Kd3 Rd1+
50. Ke3 Re1+ 51. Kf3 Rd1 52. Bd3 Kg7 53. Ke3 Re1+ 54. Be2 Ra1 55. Bf3 (55. Rb5
$2 Ra3+ 56. Bd3 Be1 57. Rxd5 Bxf2+ $1 {leads to an unclear rook endgame.})
55... Ra2 (55... Re1+ 56. Kd3) 56. Bxd5 Be1 57. Rb7 Bxf2+ (57... Rxf2 58. Rb1
$18) 58. Kf3 {Prosaic, though I could have made a spectacular king march.} (58.
Kf4 $1 $18 Ra5 59. Rxf7+ Kh8 60. Rd7 Bxd4 61. Kf5 $1 Ra3 (61... Ra7 62. Bb7)
